> in working through the Bechtel data a few points came up that seemed wort=
h
> reverting with you on:
>
> 1) As you know, the initial test group was very small, which had an
> outsized impact on our algo's ability to limit participants' being asked
> about each other. We're excited to see how the next cohort does but wante=
d
> to reiterate that we expect better results on this front simply by virtue
> of size.
>
> 2) In reviewing where/how to create the biggest impact with the next
> cohort (~180 people) we agree that picking a discreet target for change i=
s
> the right approach. As we reviewed the existing question set we think
> you'll get the biggest impact by being very activity-specific in the
> language of the questions. A conversation would probably be easiest to
> demonstrate this once you know what targets for change you'd like to set
> for the next round; let us know when and let's set a time to work through
> the question sets specifically.
>
> 3) Dynamically allowing people to be asked about people they're actively
> working with: we reviewed our existing survey allocation system and can
> certainly support a weighting from outside sources such as Microsoft
> Insights. Can you give us an example of the kind of data you could readil=
y
> export and we'll see how easily we can support integration?
>
>
> Finally, a quick heads up on D&I; this is one area you'd mentioned as
> being a target in our past calls. We're seeing a number of companies who
> systematically overlook diversity by ignoring *types of work*. In other
> words, most leadership begin using upskilling tools with other leaders, a=
nd
> increasingly limit access as they go down the corporate hierarchy. Beyond
> being bad D&I thinking, this reinforces disparities in advancement access=
,
> exacerbates racial and class divisions, and obfuscates cultural mismatch
> issues.
>
> Because IndigoMetrics produces superior metrics, we'd suggest you conside=
r
> using messaging around  equivalent measurement as a way to foster
> inclusion. If you're deciding what to measure using a full stack approach
> you're going to produce D&I messaging simply by virtue of the invitation =
to
> participate, especially if you clarify that the insights produced have
> impact across (or up and down) the organization. This is something we're
> seeing create good results in other companies, and it seems particularly
> salient to Bechtel given the breadth of your workforce.
>
> Let me know if you have any questions on the above and/or if I should
> follow up on any points with anyone else!
>
> All best,
> Josh
